		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Hyperkin makes the Hyper Click optical mouse for Super NES.<br /><br /><a href="https://www.hyperkin.com/snes-hyper-click-retro-style-mouse-hyperkin.html" class="postlink">Product description</a><br /><a href="https://www.amazon.com/Hyperkin-Hyper-Click-Retro-super-nintendo/dp/B0734BCWS1" class="postlink">Purchase</a> (Hyperkin does not appear to sell directly to end users)<br /><br />Press covfefe:<br /><a href="https://www.digitaltrends.com/computing/hyperkin-snes-mouse-replica/" class="postlink">&quot;The SNES mouse lives again, with a few modern improvements&quot; by Jon Martindale</a><br /><a href="https://www.pcmag.com/news/354676/hyperkin-launching-an-optical-mouse-for-snes" class="postlink">&quot;Hyperkin Launching an Optical Mouse for SNES&quot; by Matthew Humphries</a><br /><a href="https://www.vg247.com/2017/06/29/peripheral-maker-hyperkin-is-releasing-a-retro-style-snes-mouse/" class="postlink">&quot;Peripheral maker Hyperkin is releasing a retro style SNES mouse&quot; by Shabana Arif</a><br /><br />The project by tpw_rules got put on indefinite hiatus when tpw_rules went away to college.

		

